1. Availability (Uptime)
Metric: http.requests.success / http.requests.total

Use Case: Ensures APIs like /auth/login, /orders, /quotes are available.

Example SLO: 99.9% of login requests succeed over 30 days.

2. Latency (Performance)
Metric: http.request.duration (APM traces or custom metrics)

Use Case: Measures how fast critical endpoints respond.

Example SLO: 95% of order placement requests complete in <500ms.

3. Error Rate
Metric: http.requests.error / http.requests.total

Use Case: Tracks server-side errors (5xx, failed workflows).

Example SLO: ≤0.1% of portfolio requests fail.

4. Correctness (Data Integrity)
Metric: Custom metric from Synthetic tests (e.g., JSON body contains "assets")

Use Case: Ensures responses are valid and complete.

Example SLO: 99.9% of portfolio responses contain valid data.

5. Workflow Success
Metric: Synthetic multistep test success rate (synthetics.test.success)

Use Case: End-to-end trading flow (login → portfolio → order → status → quotes).

Example SLO: 99% of workflows succeed across all steps
